
@startuml
' E-Home-2020 Class Diagram

class Sensor {
  -vendorId: String
  -description: String
  -unit: Unit (CELSIUS, WATT)
  -roomId: String
  +getLatestValue(): Value
}

class TemperatureSensor {
  -minValue: Float
  -maxValue: Float
}

class PowerSensor {
  -totalConsumption: Float
}

class Room {
  -id: String
  -description: String
}

class Apartment {
  -address: String
  -rooms: Set<Room>
  -inhabitants: Set<Inhabitant>
  -email: String
}

class Inhabitant {
  -username: String
  -password: String
  -isAdmin: Boolean
  +login(username: String, password: String): Boolean
  +setThreshold(sensorId: String, threshold: Float): void
  +configureSensor(sensorId: String, roomId: String, description: String): void
}

class Value {
  -timestamp: DateTime
  -value: Float
}

class SensorController {
  -sensors: Map<String, Sensor>
  -apartments: Map<String, Apartment>
  +addSensor(sensor: Sensor): void
  +addApartment(apartment: Apartment): void
  +getSensorValues(sensorId: String): List<Value>
  +getLastValue(sensorId: String): Value
}

class EMonitor {
  +checkThresholds(apartmentId: String): void
  +sendAlert(email: String, message: String): void
}

' Associations and Aggregations

Sensor <|-- TemperatureSensor
Sensor <|-- PowerSensor

Apartment "1" *-- "many" Room
Apartment "1" *-- "many" Inhabitant

SensorController "1" *-- "many" Sensor
SensorController "1" *-- "many" Apartment

Inhabitant --> SensorController : login
Inhabitant --> SensorController : setThreshold
Inhabitant --> SensorController : configureSensor

SensorController --> Value : stores
Sensor --> Value : has values

SensorController --> EMonitor : notifies
EMonitor --> SensorController : checks thresholds
EMonitor --> Inhabitant : sends alert via email
@enduml

---

### 🔍 Explanation of Key Elements in the Diagram:

- **`Sensor`**: Abstract base class with common attributes like `vendorId`, `description`, `unit`, and `roomId`.
- **`TemperatureSensor` & `PowerSensor`**: Concrete sensor types that extend `Sensor` and have their own specific attributes.
- **`Room`**: Contains a description and is part of an apartment.
- **`Apartment`**: Contains multiple rooms and inhabitants. It also has an optional email address for alerts.
- **`Inhabitant`**: Users of the system who can log in, view sensor data, set thresholds, and configure sensors if they are admins.
- **`Value`**: Represents a measured value with a timestamp and numeric value.
- **`SensorController`**: Central component that manages sensors, apartments, and user access.
- **`EMonitor`**: External system that monitors thresholds and sends alerts when necessary.

